{"key":"post-13782447","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>13782447</id>\n<content>Why would you be heating a fruiting chamber?&amp;nbsp; Cubes fruit perfectly at normal indoor room temperature.&amp;nbsp; Standing water is a breeding ground for everything we hate, and the peroxide isn't going to be active for long at all.&amp;nbsp; You'd be better off to ditch the heating pads, ditch the halogen light, ditch the standing water, and use well drained perlite for humidity.&amp;nbsp; Get a fluorescent lamp in the 6500K range and put it as close to the terrarium as possible without causing excess heating.&amp;nbsp; Placing your light to the side is better than directly above.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>13785342</next>\n<prev>13782199</prev>\n<first>13781137</first>\n<last>17096033</last>\n<when>1294971269</when>\n<utime>01/14/11 04:14 AM</utime>\n</post>"}